<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-12T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-10-12T21:00:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5611: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-13T10:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 13,
                                        1924—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 13—2:43
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>… source of most reliable police information during war states that
                            Generals Lu and Ho have deserted possibly going about 3 a.m. today. Will
                            report later whether confirmation obtained.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>